# RC Grass Cutting Rover

## Overview
The RC Grass Cutting Rover is a remote-controlled robotic vehicle designed for grass-cutting applications. The rover combines embedded systems, motor control, and wireless communication to provide efficient and safe lawn maintenance.

## Features
- Remote-controlled operation
- Grass-cutting mechanism using DC motor
- Obstacle detection using sensors
- Arduino-based control system
- Battery-powered mobile platform
- Four-wheel drive for better terrain handling

## Hardware Components
- Arduino Uno/Nano
- L298N Motor Driver
- DC Gear Motors
- Grass Cutting Motor
- Ultrasonic Sensor
- RF/Bluetooth Control Module
- Rechargeable Battery Pack
- Chassis and Wheels

## Software
- Arduino IDE
- Embedded C/C++
- Serial Communication Libraries

## Working Principle
The rover receives commands from a remote controller and moves accordingly. A high-speed motor drives the cutting blade to trim grass. Sensors help detect obstacles and improve operational safety.

## Applications
- Lawn maintenance
- Garden grass cutting
- Agricultural field maintenance
- Robotics and embedded systems projects

